(power_switching, time).explanation: Switching power and execution time are independent metrics where switching power represents energy consumption per cycle while time represents total execution duration;

(power_switching, power_clock).explanation: Switching power and clock power are separate components of total power consumption that operate independently in digital circuits;

(power_switching, area_net_area).explanation: Larger interconnect areas increase wire capacitance which directly increases the switching power required to charge and discharge these capacitive loads;
